h the Colts’ drops being the remaining four. That’s a completely specified chance model under which we can simulate data. So it’s the ","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"key":"hQTLAqsio8"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"null hypothesis","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"key":"tsPXFtfD2N"}],"key":"gKxTplp4WW"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"key":"OHqlNV1wkV"}],"key":"FqKhJxl2cy"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For the alternative, we can take the position that the Patriots’ drops are too large, on average, to resemble a random sample drawn from all the drops.","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"OH6tqaqI0H"}],"key":"OjfQ3cMbHA"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Test Statistic","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"YlVqTymY7Z"}],"identifier":"test-statistic","label":"Test Statistic","html_id":"test-statistic","implicit":true,"key":"q2p55YH1lU"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A natural statistic is the difference between the two average drops, which we will compute as “average drop for Patriots - average drop for Colts”. Large values of this statistic will favor the alternative hypothesis.","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"jfyjROzWp6"}],"key":"QvjYFqDml4"}],"key":"DV3uuW1juR"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"observed_means = football.group(